



SHORTCUTS
to play (on mac) - option/return 
to stop (on mac) - option/return/.


DRUMS
bd - bass drum 
sd - snare drum 
hh - high hats
~ - rests 
.bank("RolandTR808") - bank for different types of drum kits 

VOCALS
numbers:1 - female voice announces number (cool aura)

VARIATIONS 
instrument:1 - different variations of the instrument 

NOTES
note("c4 d e f g a") - basic notes 
.oct(-1) - octive of the notes 

SOUNDS
sound("hh * 3") // high hats * repetitions per cycle 

N NOTATION 
n("0 1 [4 2] 3*2").s(jazz) - equivalent to s("jazz jazz:1 [jazz:4 jazz:2] jazz:3*2")


SUBSEQUENCES 
s("jass [rim jazz] ~ hh") - splits the second step into two substeps. nested sub sequences allowed. 
    note: [hh hh hh] === hh*3

SELECTIVE NOTES
s("bd rim/2 mt lt") - only plays rim every 2nd cycle

TIMING
setcps(0.5) - default 0.5 cps, sets the duration of the cycle  
setcps(130/60/4) - for 130 BPM 

ONE STEP PER CYCLE 
s("<bd ht>") - each element lasts for a full cycle



REPETITION (STEPS)
s("bd hh!3") - repeats hh 3x with equivalent beat to bd, same as "bd hh hh hh"

ELONGATION (STEPS) 
s("rim mt@3") - same as "rim mt ~ ~"

SPEEDING UP (STEPS)
s("mt lt*3") - same as "mt [lt lt lt]"


POLY RHYTHMS
s("<[lt ht mt], [rim casio] [rim casio rim]>*2") - polyphony: commas layer patterns
s("[jazz casio rim, hh hh:2]*2) - polyrhythms: [] cycles align, subsequences repeat at the same rate (all sequences will have the same length)
s("{jazz casio rim, hh hh:2}*2") - polymeters: {} steps align (same step duration) but different loop lengths (when shorter sequence ends it loops back to the beginningâ‰¥)

